reviewText: This is a great video for the tractor loving kid. My bunch are just into transportation. We've got Thomas, Theodore and Jay-Jay and now a super entertaining video about tractor characters in John Deere Heaven inspiring a lot of imagination in our house.
The children really love this video if they love John Deere tractors.  It also shows trains so it covers two areas boys adore.

This is a great video for the tractor loving kid. My bunch are just into transportation. We've got Thomas, Theodore and Jay-Jay and now a super entertaining video about tractor characters in John Deere Heaven inspiring a lot of imagination in our house.
The children really love this video if they love John Deere tractors.  It also shows trains so it covers two areas boys adore.
My grandsons watch it over and over.
Very entertaining for children.  Lots of music.  Our 3 yr. old grandson enjoyed it.

Although there are parts that are little cheesy, my four year old son watches it every chance he gets.  If your child liked the other John Deere videos, they will not stop talking about this one either!

This movie is on constant rotation. Well recorded. If you kid likes tractors they will like this video. Like all kids movies though the parents go batty after a while listening to the songs over and over. Overall a great value.
My grandson just loved this movie great for kids has lots of action trains tractors songs educational content great dvd

I watched this with three grandsons, 10, 8, 6. It must be for younger kids. Its all toys on a set that's about as good as U-Tube. If you watch close you'll see the tractors 'pulled' across the field with string. I bought it at the John Deere dealer for $20. The kids watched half of it - once.

My three year old son adored the tractor dvd's, but this dvd just doesn't seem to interest him, and he loves trains. The DVD is also made fairly cheap and at times will not play in our DVD player. We have no problems with other DVD's so I know it's not our player.
